<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-09-02T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-09-02T11:00:00-05:00" n="463" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">865.4016/55: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-02T17:00:00+01:00">September 2, 1938—5
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 2—2:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>225. My telegram No. 223, September 1, 6 p.m. The Council of
                                Ministers today approved a Decree Law excluding all persons both of
                                whose parents were of the Jewish race from the teaching profession
                                in general and barring such persons from admission to all schools
                                and institutions of learning recognized by the State. A transitional
                                exception is made in the cases of those previously enrolled in the
                                universities who will be permitted to continue their studies.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>